According to Forbes the 3 best-selling franchises are Japanese, and the two best-selling Japanese franchises sold more than all the non-Japanese games that appear on the 16 best-selling franchises list(the top non-Japanese games are: The Sims(U.S), Lineage(Korean), Madden Football(U.S), Grand Theft Auto(U.K), Age of Empires(U.S), Warcraft(U.S), Diablo(U.S), Halo(U.S))<a href="Games.html#1">[1]</a><br/<br/>

"In 2002, it is estimated that Japan accounted for nearly 50% of the world's gaming market. That has now fallen to around 10%"<a href="Games.html#2">[2]</a><br/><br/>

